OL,3,CPolls close in an election that could
OL,4,Cshape politics for some time
OL,6,FKeir Starmer and his wife Victoria,
OL,7,Fcast their votes at Westminster Chapel
OL,8,Fin central London on Thursday morning.
OL,10,FLib Dem leader Ed Davey and his wife
OL,11,FEmily cast their votes at Surbiton
OL,12,FHill Methodist Church in south-west
OL,13,FLondon.
OL,15,FConservative leader Kemi Badenoch and
OL,16,Fher husband Hamish cast their votes at
OL,17,FClavering Village Hall in Saffron
OL,18,FWalden.
OL,20,FReform UK's Nigel Farage cast his vote
OL,21,Fin Walton-on-the-Naze, Essex.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
