OL,3,CPolls close in an election that could
OL,4,Cshape politics for some time
OL,6,FIn Wales, Labour could lose control of
OL,7,Fthe Senedd for the first time since
OL,8,Fits creation.
OL,10,FNationalist party Plaid Cymru is
OL,11,Ffighting for control against Reform,
OL,12,Fmeaning a strong showing for both
OL,13,Fparties could push Labour into third.
OL,15,FIn Scotland, the SNP looked set to be
OL,16,Fthe largest party, with Reform and
OL,17,FLabour both fighting for second place,
OL,18,Fhoping to take the runner-up position
OL,19,Ffrom the Conservatives, who currently
OL,20,Fhave the second most seats in Holyrood.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
